JOHANNESBURG, October 3 – Melania Trump has opened her first big solo international trip as US first lady  with a wave, a smile and a baby in her arms, aiming to promote child welfare during a five-day tour of Africa, AP reported.  We are taking off for #Africa! So looking forward to visiting #Ghana #Malawi #Kenya & #Egypt as I take #BeBest international. #FLOTUSinAfrica2018 pic.twitter.com/8P7r0evXcU — Melania Trump (@FLOTUS) October 1, 2018  She arrived in the West African nation of Ghana on Tuesday after an overnight flight from Washington and quickly made her way to the Greater Accra Regional Hospital. – African News Agency (ANA)